items.name: Gun2Head Pose
items.description:
V4 SUMMARY

In the attempt to revisit this and make it better, V4 of this concept has now attained better functionality when generating handguns. It also no longer has the issue of switching hands or using both hands; it will always generate the pose on the righthand side.

Unfortunately, it was a consistently unavoidable price I had to pay that the fingergun only mode became more scuffed than the gun mode, unlike the previous version. It's trained to do two fingers instead of just one, yet still prefers to do one anyway.

Note that the images it generates are almost always a bit too detailed, and most outputs you will get look semireal.

It does relatively well without controlnet, though that is not to say controlnet cannot help make it better, especially when trying for fingerguns, where it often lowers the hand or places it in front of the forehead. If it isn't giving you the pose, it's fine to increase the weight past one a bit.

V3 SUMMARY

Well, I tried to make this work, but I won't lie, you WILL have to wrestle with this to get what you want. This lora is designed to work with both guns and finger guns, all you have to do is prompt as such. However, I've tried everything, but it will, no matter what and whenever it wants to, give two guns to the head instead of just one. You can use as many negative prompts as you'd like but it won't get rid of it forever. I've retrained it multiple times, but that didn't work either. So in the end, since it still technically does what it's meant to, I'm still gonna post it anyway.

If you manage to find a way to prevent the issue completely, please do let me know. Also, this doesn't seem to mix well with other loras, but take that with a grain of salt, because that happens no matter what loras I use, so it's maybe just a personal problem. Another thing is that getting two fingers instead of one is also difficult, though sometimes increasing the weight just slightly fixes that.

A negative prompt you can try:

(gun, holding gun, weapon, holding weapon:1.4), dual wielding, double finger guns

Keep in mind the previews may look good, but are cherry-picked results over a wide range of tests. Therefore...Do not expect full replication!

At the end I've provided examples as to what can go wrong.

66 images, trained on NAI. Tested across multiple models.

items.name: Karyl (Princess Connect! Re:Dive) Character LoRA
items.description:
A LoRA that has been trained to generate fairly accurate images of the character Karyl from the anime and mobile game Princess Connect! Re:Dive. Like my previous LoRA, it is not trained for NSFW but performs relatively well when used with NSFW prompts. It was created based on the NovelAI model, but also works well with the AnythingV3 model, as featured in a few of the images. Other models have not been tested, but shouldn't cause much of an issue. The dataset provided contained 30 images of the character featured in official art, anime scenes, with a few works from unaffiliated artists.

Note: Sometimes it likes to try to produce images of Karyl with slightly pinkish hair and eyes that lean toward a yellowish-green. This can be fixed by adding the prompts "black hair" and "green eyes". It also doesn't always add cat ears 100% of the time, so you can use the prompt "cat ears" to specify them.

Good prompts to use:

Masterpiece, best quality, highres, cat ears, black hair, green eyes,

Negative prompts to use:

lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, text, error, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, bad face, ugly face, extra limbs, bad arms, ugly eyes, extra tail

items.name: SonicEdge's Akeno Himejima
items.description:
My second Embedding.

This is a Textual Inversion of Akeno Himejima (highschool dxd). I had some trouble with this and if I'm going to be honest I still get issues with some gens, but it's fine more often than not.
Trained on 84 samples with 5000 steps.
Works for both NSFW and SFW, and has more leeway for positions than my Rias embedding, likely due to less sample images.

Works best with hires fix and some prompts such as masterpiece, 2k and a negative prompt embedding ect.

I have plans to create these as embeddings:

- Kuoh Acadamy uniform (done, uploading next)
- Rias embedding with her uniform (Not doing this, decided to just make the uniform separate and leave it at that.)
- Other DxD characters (Irina and Xenovia planned next in the series of DxD characters)
- Specific poses
- Certain fetishes
- More interesting positions

I would love to see the stuff you can generate with Akeno.

Additional notes: All examples were made using Corneos 7th heaven model (Corneo's 7th Heaven Mix | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai)
And NAIs VAE.
Prompts are:
masterpiece, highres, details, nsfw, sonicedges_akeno_himejima, Clothing, Clothing print, mood, Bodyframing, look, Angle, Pose, bg. (Bold text are wildcards)
Negative: a negative embedding called bad_prompt_version2 that I forget the source for

Sampling steps: 20
CFG Scale: 7
WxH: 384x384 with hires fix 2x upscale to 768x768

Edit: You'll likely need to use more negative prompts to fine tune the results.

items.name: Iron Bull (Dragon Age)
items.description:
This LoRA is trained on the Iron Bull, a Qunari mercenary from Bioware video game Dragon Age: Inquisition. The dataset is 57 pics, including in-game screenshots, offical concept arts, fanarts, and pictures of fan-made 3d model.

Base model is AbyssOrangeMix2-nsfw, but should work on other model too, especially NAI-based ones. I tested it on AOM2-7thV3_C_40 and AOM3. It works well with style LoRA too.

The trigger word is "iron bull". For a look closer to the character, I recommend adding "iron bull, horns, grey skin, eyepatch" into the prompt.

Note that because I didn't use a unique token when training, when using this LoRA with general model like SD 1.5, you might want to add "cattle, ox, cow" into negative prompt, in order to avoid generating a literal bull.

Join us in the #men-only channel on Unstable Diffusion Discord server, for lively discussion of how to make good men with Stable Diffusion. You can find my style LoRAs, along with other men-focused LoRAs made by other amazing people, in the #LoRa thread of this channel.

items.name: Cartoon - Jen Rejt - Korcsmros
items.description:
This is my first attempt at creating a LoRA.

Jen Rejt (29 March 1905 1 January 1943) was a Hungarian journalist, pulp fiction writer and playwright. His novels were raised above mediocrity by his inimitable and bizarre sense of humour. His novels parodying the French Foreign Legion, written under the pseudonym P. Howard, reaped the greatest success.
Pl Korcsmros (Budapest, 22.05.1916 24.05.1975), Hungarian graphic artist, book illustrator, comic book artist. Korcsmros was able to distort the realistic style to such a grotesque level that he became the most skilled draftsman of the Rejt novels.

The original, black-and-white, ink-drawn blocks were reworked, colored and painted by Zsolt H. Garisa and Zoltn Varga "Zerge". You can see this incredibly unique style.

Just remember to set CLIP skip to 2. I recommend setting the weight to between 0.8-1.1. 0.8 and below tends to be too weak, and 1.2 is probably too strong. Of course, depending on your prompts and model, your mileage may vary.

Future tasks and plans:

  • vehicles

  • female characters

  • detailed faces


I hope you enjoy it and are able to create beautiful things that bring joy to your life!

If not specified, characters are usually seen in French Foreign Legion military dress, but other clothes may be used if properly called for.

If you want to support me, you can find my work here. Thanks for sharing them: https://twitter.com/mp3Pintyo

Melina (Elden Ring) LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon or feel free to buy me a coffee

One of my favorite characters for one of my favorite games. This one was complicated because of the tattoo and the inconsistencies in the dataset. I left some tricks in the example images. Mostly requires 0.8 weight to get the eye right if you're generating full body or upper body images, for portraits and close ups 0.65 weight should be fine. Trigger is melina \(elden ring\) and should work on most booru based models and beyond. For the examples I used AnyPastel, AnyLoRA and AbyssOrangeMix2. You should get good results as long as you know what you're doing.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

Keep in mind when using it that it was trained on 6GB VRAM so the embedding might not be as good as other ones on this website but you can still get satisfactory results.

The example images were created with AbyssOrangeMix2 (hard) and I was using 0.75 weight but feel free to experiment with other weights and models. This might be model-specific but it is much better at making women than men. For the NSFW images i have also been using a couple of Corneo's textual inversion embeddings as well as JustNeutral's ShyLily embedding and it seems to be merging pretty well.

To change the weight just change the '1' in this prompt: <lora:ORIHARA:1>.

I'd love to see the art you guys make with it so feel free to add them in comments.

items.name: Haruno Sakura (Naruto) LoRA
items.description:
Haruno Sakura (Naruto - all series) LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon or feel free to buy me a coffee

There was already a LoRA for this, but people still requested it. I've asked Satyam (the author of the first Sakura LoRA) if that's fine for me to post this. If he somehow decided that it's not cool I'll simply remove it.

Back to the LoRA, this can do all versions of Sakura, from her child version with long hair, to her Boruto adult version. It can also control her forehead mark by simply adding forehead mark to the prompt (yep, the one in the example is not inpainted). To control her version you can use descriptive tags + the tags of the series she's from (see the examples). I suggest around 0.6 weight and triggers with haruno sakura. You can also have her wear any outfit you can think of simply changing the prompts. Examples made with AnyPastel and AbyssOrangeMix2. One is using my Sam Yang LoRA.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: InkSketchColour1
items.description:
Trained for SD 2.1. v2-1_768-ema-pruned.ckpt specifically.

Contains 16 vectors.

Creates colorized environment lineart. Trained on concept art images of interior environment lineart. Works okay with other subject matter, but has a tendency to skew image output towards objects with angular features/and or adds buildings to the scene.

2 Versions, Standard and subtle.

Subtle is the same embedding with the vector values lowered, which seems to have a different effect than turning down the token within the prompt (InkSketchcolour:0.5) for example. It preforms better on non-architectural subject matter.

Place late in prompt. Made to be mixed with other paintsyles. Pairs well with laxpeintv2, vray-render, cardstyle.

For best effect: <subject matter here> InkSketchColour1 <other paint effects here> InkSketchColour1Subtle

Repeating the token helps maintain the effect, otherwise the lineart tends to be lost.

items.name: MobiusZen's In-Between Expiramental Mixes (each unique)
items.description:
I'm mixing a ton of stuff to experiment, mostly aiming for a stylized 3D hoping for a unique style that comes from merging other styles, I figured I could share some of the better in between mixes as I go here. Each one will be different than others so the mixes are often not related, also I've really only tested these a bit to prod for what style they do on portraits, more testing needed for how they can do other things.

I figure my options are to share or not share, so this my attempt at sharing some of the steps along the process.

modelVersions.name: StylizR-MarvelWhatIf
modelVersions.description: This is a 50/50 mix of Marvel What if and StylizR, the focus was on making a more 3D looking version of Marvel What If, but I think it came out fairly charming on it's own. Below are the test images, prompt keyword was "a mix of whatif style and tdst style"

modelVersions.name: DarkestDungeon-JOJO-Clonewars
modelVersions.description: Mix of Models of Darkest Dungeon, Jojo and Clonewars. Attempt was to create a new style in 3D with strong linework, not a failure in that it fairly well made a 3D version of Jojo Style, but also wasn't what was expected. ran prompt "mix of darkest dungeon style and darkestdungeon style and clonewars style and clone wars style and jojo style and newstl"

modelVersions.name: Cute3DJomad-SamDoesUlt
modelVersions.description: Combination of Models "Cute3d Style Reference" and "JoMad Diffusion" and "Samdoesarts Ultmerge". This was with a focus of getting a kind of 3D version of the SamDoes Style, but a little different. Usually ran it with keywords "a mix of (keyword1) and (keyword2) etc"

modelVersions.name: Comic-Redshift
modelVersions.description: An Attempt to get a comic style to turn out 3D, so a mix of Comic Diffusion and Redshift, I think it turned out quite well. I usually ran it with "mix of (keyword1) and (keyword 2)" but this model made interesting things without keywords too.

modelVersions.name: Telltale-BorderlandsMix
modelVersions.description: Telltale and Borderlands (both of them) mix, came out surprisingly better than expected and shaped most of my future mixes. I usually ran it with mix of (trigger word1) and (trigger word 2) etc.

modelVersions.name: DC Anim - Clone Wars Mix
modelVersions.description: Mix of DC Animated and Clone Wars Models (both of them). An attempt to get the DC style to show up in 3D (because often if you water down a 2D model a little the style will come through in 3D). Not really a failure or success but a step towards a future mix hence it's here.

items.name: Ares Mix
items.description:
Attention: You need to get your own VAE to use this model to the fullest. While it does work without a VAE, it works much better with one. I recommend you try this one out.

Hey everyone. After GrapeLikeDreamFruit hit, I started missing having a more general purpose model for the mundane kind of pictures - nude photographs on different backgrounds and some light hardcore capabilities. This model here is my response to that need. It handles the female nude superbly, and while it's less of an artistic model than GrapeLike, it's still quite capable in that regard. It's quite good at hardcore, even if that is just a secondary goal for this model, and can be prompted for a variety of acts. Model has a good response to Danbooru tags.

This model involves dreamlike photoreal, so here is the license that you must abide by.

See examples for some ideas.

Deeper explanation:

This model merge was done following a similar phylosophy to GrapeLike: a Block merge between a realistic anatomy + skin core and a posing anime core. The block merge is done in such a way as to emphasize the anime core in the center of the Unet, while rapidly decaying back to the realistic core at the edges. This has the effect of bringing a lot of posing and composition ideas from hentai models inside the photorealistic core we have available without touching textures and photorealism. Full recipe follows:

Anatomy core:

izumi, F222, dreamlike photoreal, realistic vision 1.2, sxd, all at the same intensity. ie, the merge chain was:
(((izumi + F222 0.5) + dreamlike photoreal 0.33) + realistic vision 0.25) + sxd 0.2

Anime core:

Anything v4.5 merged with Basil Mix using the same block merge coefficients used in mixing Abyss Orange Mix, then merged 40% with grapefruit, the result was merged 30% with gape60 and finally 15% with RPG v4.

Bringing both together:

The block merge for both was done using a formula. I kept the bottleneck Model A was anatomy, model B was anime. I kept the center lalyer at 0.7, as well as base alpha, then followed 0.8/(n**1.1)as a merge rule, with n being distance from the center. Full numbers were "0.05199847612695355,0.05722134125067434,0.06354625877794251,0.07135480548979826,0.08122523963562354,0.09407671474206218,0.11146117361039158,0.13621438760332552,0.17411011265922482,0.23892225595753655,0.373213196614723,0.8,0.7,0.8,0.373213196614723,0.23892225595753655,0.17411011265922482,0.13621438760332552,0.11146117361039158,0.09407671474206218,0.08122523963562354,0.07135480548979826,0.06354625877794251,0.05722134125067434,0.05199847612695355".

modelVersions.name: v0.2
modelVersions.description:
This version includes a completely redone anime posing core. Exact details about how to reproduce that merge can be found in the page for that version.

Things that are different:

  • Model no longer trends towards asian women. This happens because Basil Mix is no longer a part of the mix.

  • Breasts are smaller by default. You can still prompt for gigantic hanging tits if you want to, and you will get them.

  • Noise offset is baked into the model for low key lighting. Sources were iCoMix and Cine Diffusion.

Things that are better:

  • Model is more consistent and more responsive to prompts. It's also less biased towards NSFW (while still biased towards it). Unprompted penetration is a thing of the past.

  • More capable in fantasy and horror situations, better backgrounds.

  • Anatomy, especially genitals, is much improved. Hardcore capabilities are also much better.

  • Easier posing, better emotional response from subjects. Also more varied faces, though not improved by much.

Things that are worse:

  • More difficult to get standard people. The first version was very good in getting non-super-model women. It now trends a bit more towards Hollywood pretty. Regular looking women require prompting.

  • NSFW stuff and nudity are not necessarily default in this version, so if you want someone nude, you will likely have to prompt for it.

  • Feet. I'm sorry to all feet people, but you probably want to prompt for socks / shoes.

Merge Details:
Obtained by fusing the photoreal anatomy core (unmodified) with the anime core using the Merge Block Weighted extension for Auto1111 with the following weights:
"0.05199847612695355,0.05722134125067434,0.06354625877794251,0.07135480548979826,0.08122523963562354,0.09407671474206218,0.15,0.25,0.4,0.6,0.6,0.8,1.0,0.8,0.6,0.6,0.4,0.25,0.15,0.09407671474206218,0.08122523963562354,0.07135480548979826,0.06354625877794251,0.05722134125067434,0.05199847612695355"

base alpha set to 1.0

Full list of models used:

Anatomy:

  • Izumi

  • F222

  • Dreamlike Photoreal

  • Realistic Vision 1.2

  • SXD

Anime:

  • cine diffusion (yes, it's in this block)

  • iCoMix v3

  • Counterfeit v2.5

  • gape60

As always, there is a special license attached to dreamlike derivatives. You can find a link to that in the model card.
